text: Alina Zmushka (born 5 January 1997) is a Belarusian swimmer. She competed in the women's 100 metre breaststroke at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian female swimmers Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Swimmers at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Female breaststroke swimmers
